### Generate RSS, Atom, and JSON Feeds in Node.js

Source: https://github.com/jpmonette/feed/blob/master/README.md

This comprehensive example illustrates how to initialize a Feed instance, configure its metadata, add individual content items (posts), categories, and contributors. It then shows how to output the generated feed in RSS 2.0, Atom 1.0, and JSON Feed 1.0 formats, showcasing the core API for content syndication.

```javascript
import { Feed } from "feed";

const feed = new Feed({
  title: "Feed Title",
  description: "This is my personal feed!",
  id: "http://example.com/",
  link: "http://example.com/",
  language: "en", // optional, used only in RSS 2.0, possible values: http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/struct/dirlang.html#langcodes
  image: "http://example.com/image.png",
  favicon: "http://example.com/favicon.ico",
  copyright: "All rights reserved 2013, John Doe",
  updated: new Date(2013, 6, 14), // optional, default = today
  generator: "awesome", // optional, default = 'Feed for Node.js'
  feedLinks: {
    json: "https://example.com/json",
    atom: "https://example.com/atom"
  },
  author: {
    name: "John Doe",
    email: "johndoe@example.com",
    link: "https://example.com/johndoe"
  }
});

posts.forEach(post => {
  feed.addItem({
    title: post.title,
    id: post.url,
    link: post.url,
    description: post.description,
    content: post.content,
    author: [
      {
        name: "Jane Doe",
        email: "janedoe@example.com",
        link: "https://example.com/janedoe"
      },
      {
        name: "Joe Smith",
        email: "joesmith@example.com",
        link: "https://example.com/joesmith"
      }
    ],
    contributor: [
      {
        name: "Shawn Kemp",
        email: "shawnkemp@example.com",
        link: "https://example.com/shawnkemp"
      },
      {
        name: "Reggie Miller",
        email: "reggiemiller@example.com",
        link: "https://example.com/reggiemiller"
      }
    ],
    date: post.date,
    image: post.image
  });
});

feed.addCategory("Technologie");

feed.addContributor({
  name: "Johan Cruyff",
  email: "johancruyff@example.com",
  link: "https://example.com/johancruyff"
});

console.log(feed.rss2());
// Output: RSS 2.0

console.log(feed.atom1());
// Output: Atom 1.0

console.log(feed.json1());
// Output: JSON Feed 1.0
```

--------------------------------

### Migrate to CommonJS Require for Feed Library

Source: https://github.com/jpmonette/feed/blob/master/README.md

For environments that do not support ES6 modules, this snippet provides the updated CommonJS `require()` syntax for the 'feed' library. This is crucial for compatibility when migrating from versions older than 3.0.0.

```javascript
const Feed = require('feed').Feed;
```

--------------------------------

### Install Feed Library via Yarn

Source: https://github.com/jpmonette/feed/blob/master/README.md

This snippet demonstrates how to install the 'feed' library using Yarn, a popular package manager for JavaScript projects. It's the first step to integrate the library into your Node.js application.

```bash
$ yarn add feed
```

--------------------------------

### Migrate to ES6 Named Import for Feed Library

Source: https://github.com/jpmonette/feed/blob/master/README.md

This snippet shows the recommended ES6 named import syntax for the 'feed' library, applicable for environments that support ES6 modules. This is part of the migration process from versions older than 3.0.0.

```typescript
import { Feed } from "feed";
```

